app.use(express.json({ limit: '100kb' }));
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false, limit: '100kb' }));
```

### 2. No Helmet — Missing Security Headers

The app sets no HTTP security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `X-Frame-Options`, CSP, etc.). This exposes users to clickjacking, MIME-sniffing, and XSS attacks.

